description:
&lt;p&gt;We have great opportunity a Senior Mental Health Nurse to come and work at Solent NHS Trust. You will be working within our Community Recovery Teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have embedded recovery principles in the front line of care we provide. All of our staff are trained in, and deliver a therapy and teach in the Recovery college. We have a great ethos here and are supportive of our staff we Work to the organisational Values of Honesty, Everyone Counts, Accountability, Respect and Teamwork (HEART).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are based on the South coast Portsmouth is a vibrant city with lots of activity’s and history and beautiful coast line to explore giving you a good work life balance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You can contact Dawn Thisby on dawn.thisby@solent.nhs.uk for more information about this exciting opportunity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Previous applicants need not apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note that should this post attract sufficient interest, we may choose to close at an earlier stage. We strongly suggest that you apply at an early stage. &lt;strong&gt;If we have not contacted you within four weeks of the closing date of this post, please presume that you have not have selected.&lt;/strong&gt; Candidates selected for interview will be contacted within 2-3 weeks; therefore you should check your emails regularly including junk mail folders.&lt;/p&gt;
